3 SECTION 9. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6470.29.1 of Title 36, unless
5 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. Subject to the prior written approval of the Insurance
7 Commissioner, upon application of the sponsor and with the prior
8 consent of each participant of the affected protected cells or as
9 otherwise permitted pursuant to a participant contract, a sponsored
10 captive insurance company may convert one or more protected cells
11 into a:
12 1. Single protected cell or entity-protected cell;
13 2. New sponsored captive insurance company;
14 3. New pure captive insurance company;
15 4. New risk retention group;
16 5. New agency captive insurance company;
17 6. New industrial insured captive insurance company;
18 7. New association captive insurance company;
19 8. Captive insurance company organized as a reciprocal insurer;
20 or
21 9. Series captive insurance company.
22 B. Any such conversion requires providing the Insurance
23 Commissioner at least thirty (30) days' prior written notice, as
24 well as submitting a business plan to be approved by the Insurance
Req. No. 16196 Page 38

1 Comm issioner, without affecting any protected cell's assets, rights,
2 benefits, obligations, and liabilities.
3 C. Any such conversion shall be deemed for all purposes to be a
4 continuation of each such protected cell's existence together with
5 all of its assets, rights, benefits, obligations, and liabilities,
6 as a new protected cell, a sponsored captive insurance company, a
7 pure captive insurance company, a risk retention group, an
8 industrial insured captive insurance company, an association captive
9 insurance company, or captive insurance company formed as a
10 reciprocal insurer.
11 D. Any such conversion shall be deemed to occur without any
12 transfer or assignment of any such assets, rights, benefits,
13 obligations, or liabilities and without the creation of any
14 reversionary interest in, or impairment of, any such assets, rights,
15 benefits, obligations, and liabilities.
16 E. Any such conversion shall not be construed to limit any
17 rights or protections applicable to any converted protected cell and
18 such sponsored captive insurance company that existed immediately
19 prior to the date of any such conversion.
20 F. Any protected cell converting into an entity-protected cell
21 pursuant to this act, or converting into a new captive insurance
22 company or risk retention group pursuant to this section, shall
23 perform such conversion in accordance with:
24
Req. No. 16196 Page 39

1 1. The provisions of the Oklahoma General Corporation Act,
2 Section 1001 et seq. of Title 18 of the Oklahoma Statutes, if the
3 converted captive insurance company is to be a corporation;
4 2. The provisions of the Oklahoma Limited Liability Company
5 Act, Section 2000 et seq. of Title 18 of the Oklahoma Statutes, if
6 the converted captive insurance company is to be a limited liability
7 company; or
8 3. The provisions applicable to any other type of entity
9 permissible under Oklahoma law if the converted captive insurance
10 company is to be such an entity.
