13 SECTION 13. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6470.29.5 of Title 36, unless
15 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. Protected cell assets are available only to the creditors of
17 the sponsored captive insurance company who are creditors in respect
18 of that protected cell and entitled, in conformity with the
19 provisions of this act, to have recourse to the protected cell
20 assets attributable to that protected cell.
21 B. Protected cell assets shall be absolutely protected from the
22 creditors of the sponsored captive insurance company who are not
23 creditors in respect of that protected cell and who, accordingly,
24
Req. No. 16196 Page 45

1 are not entitled to have recourse to the protected cell assets
2 attributable to that protected cell.
3 C. Creditors with respect to a protected cell shall not be
4 entitled to have recourse against the protected cell assets of other
5 protected cells or the assets of the sponsored captive insurance
6 company's general assets.
7 D. When an obligation of a sponsored captive insurance company
8 to a person arises from a transaction, or is otherwise imposed, in
9 respect of a protected cell:
10 1. That obligation of the sponsored captive insurance company
11 shall extend only to the protected cell assets attributable to that
12 protected cell, and the person shall, in respect of that obligation,
13 be entitled to have recourse only to the protected cell assets
14 attributable to that protected cell; and
15 2. That obligation of the sponsored captive insurance company
16 shall not extend to the protected cell assets of any other protected
17 cell or the assets of the company's general assets, and that person
18 shall not, in respect of that obligation, be entitled to have
19 recourse to the protected cell assets of any other protected cell or
20 the assets of the company's general assets.
21 E. When an obligation of a sponsored captive insurance company
22 relates solely to the general assets, the obligation of the
23 sponsored captive insurance company shall extend only to, and that
24 creditor shall, in respect of that obligation, be entitled to have
Req. No. 16196 Page 46

1 reco urse only to, the assets of the sponsored captive insurance
2 company's general assets.
3 F. In no event shall the establishment of one or more protected
4 cells alone constitute or be deemed to be a fraudulent conveyance,
5 an intent by the sponsored captive insurance company to defraud
6 creditors, or the carrying out of business by the sponsored captive
7 insurance company for any other fraudulent purpose.
8 SECTION 14. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
9 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6470.29.6 of Title 36, unless
10 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
11 A. The pleadings in any legal action brought by or against a
12 sponsored captive insurance company shall specify which protected
13 cell or cells are or should be named a party to the suit. If the
14 general assets are identified in the pleading, it likewise shall be
15 separately identified in the pleadings as if it were a protected
16 cell.
17 B. A legal action brought against a sponsored captive insurance
18 company that does not specify one or more protected cells shall be
19 deemed to have been brought against the general assets only.
20 C. Any protected cell that is not named in the pleadings of the
21 legal action shall not be deemed to be a party to the legal action.
22 Any protected cell that is erroneously named as a party or named
23 without proper cause shall be entitled to prompt dismissal from the
24 legal action.
Req. No. 16196 Page 47

1 D. No protected cell has a duty to defend the rights and
2 obligations of any other protected cell.
3 E. In any legal action involving a sponsored captive insurance
4 company or a protected cell, any papers, documents, or property of a
5 nonparty protected cell shall be afforded the same status during
6 discovery as the documents or property of any other unrelated third
7 party. A nonparty protected cell shall have standing to appear and
8 petition for any appropriate relief to protect the confidentiality
9 of its papers or documents.
10 SECTION 15. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6470.29.7 of Title 36, unless
12 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 A. In connection with the rehabilitation or liquidation of a
14 sponsored captive insurance company, the assets and liabilities of a
15 protected cell shall, to the extent the receiver determines they are
16 separable, at all times be kept separate from, and shall not be
17 commingled with, those of other protected cells and the sponsored
18 captive insurance company.
19 B. Upon any order of rehabilitation or liquidation of a
20 sponsored captive insurance company, the receiver shall manage the
21 assets and liabilities of the protected cell captive insurance
22 company pursuant to this section:
23
24
Req. No. 16196 Page 48

1 1. The assets of a protected cell may not be used to pay any
2 expenses or claims other than those attributable to such protected
3 cell;
4 2. A sponsored captive insurance company's capital and surplus
5 shall at all times be available to pay any expenses of or claims
6 against the sponsored captive insurance company;
7 3. In the event of an insolvency of a sponsored captive
8 insurance company where the receiver determines that one or more
9 protected cells remain solvent, the receiver may separate such cells
10 from the sponsored captive insurance company, and may allow, on
11 application of the sponsor, for the conversion of such protected
12 cells into one or more new or existing sponsored captive insurance
13 companies with a sponsor or sponsors, or one or more other captive
14 insurance companies, pursuant to such plan or plans of operation as
15 the Insurance Commissioner deems acceptable; and
16 4. In the event of an insolvency of one or more protected cells
17 of a sponsored captive insurance company, the receiver may separate
18 such cell or cells from the sponsored captive insurance company and
19 may allow for the conversion of such protected cell or cells into
20 one or more new or existing sponsored captive insurance companies,
21 or one or more other captive insurance companies, pursuant to a plan
22 or plans of operation approved by the Insurance Commissioner.
23 C. Unless the sponsor consents and the Insurance Commissioner
24 has granted prior written approval, the assets of the sponsored
Req. No. 16196 Page 49

1 capt ive insurance company's general assets shall not be used to pay
2 any expenses or claims attributable solely to a protected cell or
3 protected cells of the sponsored captive insurance company. In the
4 event that the assets of the sponsored captive insurance company's
5 general assets are used to pay expenses or claims attributable
6 solely to a protected cell or protected cells of the sponsored
7 captive insurance company, the sponsor is not required to contribute
8 additional capital and surplus to the sponsored captive insurance
9 company's general assets, notwithstanding the provisions of Section
10 6470.6 of Title 36 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
11 SECTION 16. AMENDATORY 36 O.S. 2021, Section 6470.35, as
12 amended by Section 10, Chapter 154, O.S.L. 2022 (36 O.S. Supp. 2025,
13 Section 6470.35), is amended to read as follows:
14 Section 6470.35. A. As used in this section, "dormant captive
15 insurance company" means a captive insurance company that has:
16 1. Ceased transacting the business of insurance including the
17 issuance of insurance policies; and
18 2. No remaining liabilities associated with insurance business
19 transactions or insurance policies issued prior to the filing of its
20 application for a certificate of dormancy under this section.
21 B. A dormant captive insurance company domiciled in this state
22 that meets the criteria of subsection A of this section may apply to
23 the Insurance Commissioner for a certificate of dormancy. The
24
Req. No. 16196 Page 50

1 cert ificate of dormancy shall be subject to renewal every five (5)
2 years and shall be forfeited if not renewed within such time.
3 C. A dormant captive insurance company that has been issued a
4 certificate of dormancy shall:
5 1. Possess and thereafter maintain unimpaired, paid-in capital
6 and surplus, in a form approved by the Commissioner, of not less
7 than Twenty-five Thousand Dollars ($25,000.00) Ten Thousand Dollars
8 ($10,000.00);
9 2. Submit on or before March 1 of each year to the Insurance
10 Commissioner a report of its financial condition, verified by an
11 oath of two of its executive officers, in a the manner and form
12 prescribed by the Insurance Commissioner; and
13 3. Pay a nonrefundable annual fee of Five Hundred Dollars
14 ($500.00) Three Hundred Dollars ($300.00).
15 D. A dormant captive insurance company shall not be subject to
16 or liable for the payment of any tax under Section 6470 6470.19 of
17 this title for the initial five-year dormancy.
18 E. A dormant captive insurance company shall apply to the
