11 SECTION 17. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6470.36 of Title 36, unless
13 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 A. For purposes of this section:
15 1. "Foreign" means outside the United States, its territories,
16 or possessions;
17 2. "Foreign currency" means currency issued by a government
18 outside the United States that is recognized by the United States as
19 a legitimate government-issued currency and freely exchangeable with
20 United States currency; and
21 3. "Foreign securities" means securities that are ordinarily
22 traded on an exchange outside the United States.
23 B. A captive insurance company or an individual cell of a
24 captive insurance company may, with the approval of the Insurance
Req. No. 16196 Page 52

1 Comm issioner, include within its business plan that the company
2 will:
3 1. Receive payments of premium in a specified foreign currency
4 or foreign securities and will pay claims on insured losses in a
5 specified currency or foreign securities;
6 2. Authorize the payment of claims in a specified foreign
7 currency or foreign securities; and
8 3. Hold foreign currency or foreign securities as surplus for
9 the payment of future claims.
10 C. In determining the exchange rate between United States
11 currency and the foreign currency or foreign securities, the captive
12 insurance company shall identify in its approved business plan a
13 publicly available and reliable exchange rate index. If the
14 exchange rate index identified in the business plan is not
15 available, then the Insurance Commissioner shall determine the
16 appropriate exchange rate for the purpose of calculating the amount
17 of premium tax due.
18 D. For the purpose of calculating the amount of premium tax due
19 under this act, a policy issued by a captive insurance company
20 payable in foreign currency or foreign securities is deemed to be of
21 an equivalent value in United States currency as of the date that
22 coverage is bound and is payable in United States currency when due
23 under this act.
24
Req. No. 16196 Page 53

1 E. For captive insurance companies and protected cells that
2 have received permission pursuant to subsection B of this section,
3 all reports required to be filed with captive premium tax payments
4 shall be converted to United States currency for the reporting
5 period covered by the annual report.
6 SECTION 18. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
7 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6470.37 of Title 36, unless
8 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
9 Any public body may expend public funds to capitalize a captive
10 insurance company or to provide guaranty capital in a mutual captive
11 insurance company for the purpose of forming and operating a captive
12 insurance company.
13 SECTION 19. REPEALER 36 O.S. 2021, Section 6470.28, is
14 hereby repealed.
15 SECTION 20. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
